XEI/RWN χείρων cheírōn   khi'-rone
irregular comparative of 2556;
from an obsolete equivalent  χέρης chérēs,  (of uncertain derivation); more evil or aggravated (physically, mentally or morally) :--sorer, worse.

XLIARO/S χλιαρός chliarós   khlee-ar-os'
from  χλίω chlíō,  (to warm);
tepid:--lukewarm.

XRUSO/PRASOS χρυσόπρασος chrysóprasos   khroo-sop'-ras-os
from 5557 and  πράσον práson,  (a leek);
a greenish-yellow gem ("chrysoprase"):--chrysoprase.

YA/LLW ψάλλω psállō   psal'-lo
probably strengthened from  ψάω psáō,  (to rub or touch the surface; compare 5597);
to twitch or twang, i.e. to play on a stringed instrument (celebrate the divine worship with music and accompanying odes):--make melody, sing (psalms).

YIQURISMO/S ψιθυρισμός psithyrismós   psith-oo-ris-mos'
from a derivative of  ψίθος psíthos,  (a whisper; by implication, a slander; probably akin to 5574);
whispering, i.e. secret detraction:--whispering.

